        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2002657452" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1498997315659976984">Six students at an Ivy League college latch on to an elderly professor of Greek. They create a Greek “cult” that leads to murder and, in all, the death of three people. The story is told from the point of view of the outsider in the group: he’s the only kid from the west coast and the only one on financial aid. All the misfit characters come alive, each with his (and one her) personality. The story is told methodically, step by step, and you start to feel “this could have really happened.” A gre</span>
  <span id="freeText1498997315659976984" style="display:none">Six students at an Ivy League college latch on to an elderly professor of Greek. They create a Greek “cult” that leads to murder and, in all, the death of three people. The story is told from the point of view of the outsider in the group: he’s the only kid from the west coast and the only one on financial aid. All the misfit characters come alive, each with his (and one her) personality. The story is told methodically, step by step, and you start to feel “this could have really happened.” A great book, just a bit longer than necessary. <br><br><img src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/hostedimages/1495034228i/22778431._SX540_.jpg" width="400" height="200" alt="description" class="gr-hostedUserImg"><br><br>Photo from greekboston.com<br></span>
